  p.site-title Thump Recording
  p.site-description Thump Studios is a recording facility located in Brooklyn, NY
  a.site-link href="//thumprecording.com" target="_blank" www.thumprecording.com
  .centering
    a href="//thumprecording.com" target="_blank"
      img.ss.hidden src=image_path("thump.png")
  .site-blurb.hidden
    p Thump Recording's website is built with Ruby on Rails and hosted on Heroku with a postgres database. Thump's website uses the featherlight library, javascript, jquery and sass. Thump also uses the Soundcloud API to fetch traks, Amazon AWS S3 for asset management and Cloudfront for CDN services.

.site-div.closed#clarinet-milk-tv
  p.site-title Clarinet Milk TV
  p.site-description Internet Television
  a.site-link href="//clarinet-milk-tv.herokuapp.com" target="_blank" www.clarinetmilk.tv
  .centering
    a href="//clarinet-milk-tv.herokuapp.com" target="_blank"
      img.ss.hidden src=image_path("cmtv.png")
  .site-blurb.hidden
    p Clarinet Milk TV uses the YouTube API and a timestamp sent from your browser that fetches a video from a curated playlist so that every client who is watching at the same time will be seeing the same thing, just like watching real TV. There are no controls, you just watch. Clarinet Milk was developed in collaboration with <a href="//waymondo.com">Justin Talbott of Waymondo</a>.

